# Notificare Module

## Description

A module to integrate Notificare Push API

## Accessing the Notificare Module

To access this module from JavaScript, you would do the following:

	var Notificare = require("re.notifica.titanium");

The Notificare variable is a reference to the Module object.	

## Reference

### Notificare.launch

This is the first call you should make, when launching the app.
Configures Notificare, starts listeners for application lifecycle events

Parameters:

- config {developmentKey {String}, developmentSecret {String}, productionKey {String}, productionSecret {String}, development {Boolean} }

### Notificare.registerDevice

Registers the device with Notificare API

Parameters:

- userID (optional) {String}
- userName (optional) {String}
- callback {Function} A callback({Error})

### Notificare.getNotification

Retrieve the full notification object from Notificare API

Parameters:

- notification {String} The ID of the notification, as passed in from APNS
- callback {Function} A callback({Error},{Notification}) 

### Notificare.addDeviceTags

Adds one or more tags to the device in Notificare API

Parameters:

- tags [{String}]
- callback {Function} A callback({Error})

### Notificare.removeDeviceTag

Removes a tags from the device in Notificare API

Parameters:

- tag {String}
- callback {Function} A callback({Error})

### Notificare.clearDeviceTags

Clears tags of the device in Notificare API

Parameters:

- callback {Function} A callback({Error})

### Notificare.getDeviceTags

Gets the tags that were registered for the device in Notificare API

Parameters:

- callback {Function} A callback({Error}, [{String}])

### Notificare.reply

Sends action replies back to Notificare

Parameters:

- notification {String} The ID of the notification
- label {String} The action label
- data {Object} (optional) Action data

### Notificare.logOpenNotification

Log the opening of a notification

Parameters:

- notification {String} The ID of the notification
- inBackground {Boolean} Whether the notification was received while the app was in background, i.e., opened from Notification Center


## Usage

See sample app in example/app.js


